## 5. Runtime model

The plugin has five main components:

```text
ContractPackageLoader
        ↓
PackageValidator
        ↓
ContractSession
        ↓
ExecutorBridge
        ↓
EvidenceWriter
```

The agent framework interacts only with a hook adapter.

```text
Agent Host
   ↓
Host Hook Adapter
   ↓
ContractSession
   ↓
ExecutorBridge
   ↓
Local Executor / Connectors
```

The contract session owns execution state.

The agent only receives the current step instruction and submits the step result.

---

## 6. Public library interface

The minimal library interface:

```python
from mova_contract_plugin import (
    load_package,
    ContractSession,
    ExecutorBridge,
    EvidenceWriter,
)
```

Expected usage:

```python
package = load_package("./contract_package")

bridge = ExecutorBridge()
evidence = EvidenceWriter("./evidence.jsonl")

session = ContractSession(
    package=package,
    executor_bridge=bridge,
    evidence_writer=evidence,
)

while not session.is_done():
    instruction = session.current_instruction()
    result = agent.run(instruction)
    session.submit_result(result)
```

The agent MUST NOT receive full flow control.

